📄 SPEC-1 – Method (Part 2: Database Design)

This is the core of your product — if done right, everything (AI, analytics, payments) becomes easy.

🧱 Core Database Schema (PostgreSQL)
1. Users
users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  email TEXT UNIQUE,
  password_hash TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)
2. Subscriptions
subscriptions (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID,
  plan_type TEXT, -- '2week', '1month', '1year'
  start_date TIMESTAMP,
  end_date TIMESTAMP,
  is_active BOOLEAN
)
3. Topics

👉 VERY IMPORTANT for AI

topics (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name TEXT, -- e.g. "Road Signs"
  description TEXT
)
4. Questions
questions (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  topic_id INT,
  question_text TEXT,
  image_url TEXT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMP
)
5. Answers
answers (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  question_id INT,
  answer_text TEXT,
  is_correct BOOLEAN
)
6. Exam Sessions
exam_sessions (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id UUID,
  started_at TIMESTAMP,
  finished_at TIMESTAMP,
  score INT,
  passed BOOLEAN
)
7. User Answers (VERY IMPORTANT)
user_answers (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  session_id UUID,
  question_id INT,
  selected_answer_id INT,
  is_correct BOOLEAN
)
8. Topic Performance (AI core)
topic_performance (
  user_id UUID,
  topic_id INT,
  correct_count INT,
  wrong_count INT,
  last_updated TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, topic_id)
)
🧠 AI Personalization Logic (MVP)

This is your secret weapon (simple but powerful).

Step 1: Track Mistakes

Every time user answers:

if correct:
  correct_count += 1
else:
  wrong_count += 1
Step 2: Calculate Weakness Score
weakness_score = wrong_count / (correct_count + wrong_count)
Step 3: Generate Personalized Quiz

When user clicks “Practice”:

1. Sort topics by weakness_score DESC
2. Pick top 2–3 weakest topics
3. Select questions mostly from those topics (70%)
4. Add random questions (30%)
Step 4: Adaptive Difficulty (simple version)
If user gets 80%+ → increase randomness
If <50% → focus heavily on weak topics
💡 Why This Works

Even without “real AI”:

Feels personalized
Improves learning speed
Differentiates from ptest.uz
💳 Payment System Design (Simple MVP)
Flow:
@startuml
User -> Frontend : Select plan
Frontend -> Backend : Create order
Backend -> Payment Provider : Request payment
Payment Provider -> Backend : Confirmation
Backend -> DB : Activate subscription
@enduml
Recommendation (UZ Market)

Use:

Local providers (Payme / Click) OR
Stripe (if targeting future expansion)


